Fix segfault on startup when built with AVX (-march=native etc.)

The FastMaths SIMD helpers tell the compiler the buffers they receive are
32-byte aligned via __builtin_assume_aligned(ptr, 32). However the audio
buffers in SoundEngine (and the other engine buffers reaching these helpers)
are allocated with plain `new float[]`, which on x86-64 only guarantees
16-byte alignment.

When polyphone is compiled with AVX enabled (any -march that turns on AVX,
e.g. -march=native), GCC trusts the 32-byte promise and auto-vectorizes the
generic loops with aligned 256-bit moves (vmovaps %ymm). Whenever two such
buffers happen to differ by 16 bytes modulo 32 at runtime, the aligned move
hits a 16-byte-aligned (not 32) address and raises a general-protection fault,
crashing the audio thread at startup. Distro/baseline builds (-march=x86-64,
SSE only, 16-byte movaps) never hit this, which is why it goes unnoticed.

Correct the assumed alignment to the value new[] actually guarantees (16).
The aarch64 NEON paths are unaffected (they already use unaligned vld1q_f32),
and on modern x86 unaligned 256-bit moves cost the same as aligned ones.

--- a/core/fastmaths.cpp
+++ b/core/fastmaths.cpp
@@ -86,8 +86,8 @@

 void FastMaths::addVectors(float * __restrict a, const float * __restrict b, unsigned int size)
 {
-    a = (float*)__builtin_assume_aligned(a, 32);
-    b = (const float*)__builtin_assume_aligned(b, 32);
+    a = (float*)__builtin_assume_aligned(a, 16);
+    b = (const float*)__builtin_assume_aligned(b, 16);
     unsigned int i = 0;

 #ifdef __aarch64__
@@ -113,7 +113,7 @@

 void FastMaths::clamp(float * values, unsigned int size)
 {
-    values = (float*)__builtin_assume_aligned(values, 32);
+    values = (float*)__builtin_assume_aligned(values, 16);
     unsigned int i = 0;

 #ifdef __aarch64__
@@ -141,8 +141,8 @@

 void FastMaths::multiplyAdd(float * __restrict data, const float * __restrict dataToMultiplyAndAdd, unsigned int size, float coeff)
 {
-    data = (float*)__builtin_assume_aligned(data, 32);
-    dataToMultiplyAndAdd = (float*)__builtin_assume_aligned(dataToMultiplyAndAdd, 32);
+    data = (float*)__builtin_assume_aligned(data, 16);
+    dataToMultiplyAndAdd = (float*)__builtin_assume_aligned(dataToMultiplyAndAdd, 16);
     unsigned int i = 0;

 #ifdef __aarch64__
@@ -169,8 +169,8 @@

 void FastMaths::multiply(float * __restrict data, const float * __restrict dataToMultiply, unsigned int size, float coeff)
 {
-    data = (float*)__builtin_assume_aligned(data, 32);
-    dataToMultiply = (const float*)__builtin_assume_aligned(dataToMultiply, 32);
+    data = (float*)__builtin_assume_aligned(data, 16);
+    dataToMultiply = (const float*)__builtin_assume_aligned(dataToMultiply, 16);
     unsigned int i = 0;

 #ifdef __aarch64__
@@ -196,7 +196,7 @@

